name: Dwarvenhold Depths Background
description: Lanterns cast a warm, golden glow across the meticulously carved stone architecture of an ancient dwarven city, nestled deep within a cavernous underground realm.

name: Lumina Mine Background
description: Within a dark, foreboding mine, a single, glowing crystal illuminates a weathered wooden track that disappears into the misty depths.

name: Halloween 2025 Background
description: Happy Halloween '25!

name: Christmas 2025 Background
description: Merry Christmas '25!

name: The Embered Ravine Background
description: Nestled within a deep ravine, a fantastical city of wooden structures glows warmly, their myriad windows casting an inviting light that beckons towards the bustling tavern in the foreground.

name: The Void's Embrace
description: An ominous, swirling black hole looms in the sky, threatening to consume a fortress and its surrounding landscape of desolate, ancient-looking houses.

name: Glimmering Grotto Background
description: The interior of a massive, dark cave is illuminated by a brilliant light source at its center, highlighting the intricate details of the stalagmites and rock formations.

name: [deprecated] Halloween 2025 Background
description: Happy Halloween '25!

name: [deprecated] Christmas 2025 Background
description: Merry Christmas '25!

name: Cavernous Construction Background
description: In a vast, misty cavern, ancient-looking structures, bridges, and wooden scaffolding are built into and across towering rock formations, suggesting a grand, ongoing construction or excavation project.

name: Fuji at Night Background
description: A majestic full moon hangs over a serene, snow-capped Mount Fuji, its glow illuminating a traditional Japanese pagoda and a cherry blossom-lined bridge.

name: Crimson Blossom Temple Background
description: A traditional Japanese pagoda stands majestically amidst a vibrant landscape of vivid crimson cherry trees, their reflections shimmering on the tranquil waters below a dramatic sunset sky.

name: Goldenhoard Guardian Background
description: A massive, scaly red dragon rests upon a glittering mound of gold coins, its sharp claws and menacing glare protecting its immense treasure hoard.

name: Twitch Background
description: Twitch!

name: Neon Rain City Background
description: Under a dark, rainy sky, a futuristic cityscape glows with an overwhelming array of vibrant blue and pink neon lights, reflecting off the wet streets as pedestrians and vehicles pass by.

name: Bloodwood Crows Background
description: Several dark, ominous crows take flight and perch among the bare, twisted trees of a mysterious forest bathed in an eerie, blood-red light.

name: The Dragon's Fury Background
description: A heroic knight on horseback charges fearlessly as a colossal, fire-breathing dragon unleashes a torrent of flames across a rugged, mountainous landscape.

name: Common Gold Sack
description: A sack filled with small amount of gold.

name: Uncommon Gold Sack
description: A sack filled with a moderate amount of gold.

name: Rare Gold Sack
description: A sack filled with a large amount of gold.

name: Epic Gold Sack
description: A sack filled with a huge amount of gold.

name: Legendary Gold Sack
description: A sack filled with a massive amount of gold.

name: Miners Simple Iron Band Artifact
description: A heavy, unadorned iron band worn by apprentice miners to steady their hands and their breath in the humid depths.

name: The Apprentice's Wax Cord Artifact
description: A simple cord necklace, imbued with the ancient spirit of learning, favored by those starting their lineage history.

name: Stoneguard Brooch Artifact
description: A rugged, spiked pin used to fasten cloaks, designed to turn aside minor attacks from cave vermin and falling debris.

name: Coarse Gold Thread Loop Artifact
description: A hurriedly braided ring from low-grade gold dust, promising rudimentary luck in finding scattered coinage.

name: Gritstone Charm Artifact
description: A rough-hewn charm of volcanic stone, granting a tiny chance for protective or beneficial spells to hold true upon casting.

name: Deep Delver's Padlock Artifact
description: A small, heavy, functional brass padlock (clasp closed). The surface is simple and sturdy, with the brass showing a high polish, suggesting valuable contents.

name: Apprentice's Chisel Guard Artifact
description: A segment of thick, worn brown leather designed to wrap around two fingers. Reinforced heavily with five small, visible brass rivets across the knuckle line, etched with faint angular runes.

name: Pocket Sand Timer Artifact
description: A tiny, horizontal glass tube encased in a rugged, dark bronze frame. A small amount of fine, white sand is visible inside, slightly blurred to imply perpetual, fast motion.

name: Mud-Caked Boot Pin Artifact
description: A small, heavy pin shaped like a simple dwarven boot with a squared toe. The bronze is partially obscured by dry, light brown, caked-on dirt, symbolizing longevity and long travel.

name: Copper Ear Spool Artifact
description: A single, simple, thick copper wire shaped into a tight spiral coil, designed to be worn in the earlobe. The coil subtly catches light, suggesting it is finely tuned.

name: Deep-Vein Finder Artifact
description: A dull brass pendant, rumored to hum faintly when near veins of higher quality or magically imbued ore.

name: Ghamedu Hearth Locket Artifact
description: An antique locket engraved with a small, unextinguished flame, symbolizing the ancient endurance of the first dwellings established in Ghamedu Korg.

name: Bracer of the Second Strike Artifact
description: A reinforced leather bracer etched with runes of focus, improving the chance that a powerful strike connects with maximum force.

name: Golden Haul Amulet Artifact
description: A polished nugget set in dark brass, slightly increasing the final yield of recovered coinage and loose gems.

name: Engineer's Chronometer Artifact
description: A sturdy, gear-laden ring that subtly adjusts the wearer's rhythm to an optimal, steady digging cadence.

name: Miner's Cursing Ring Artifact
description: A wide band ring of matte black iron. The surface is etched with aggressive, angular runes of red (not glowing). The iron is dented and stressed from powerful blows.

name: The Quickening Compass Artifact
description: A circular bronze compass with a simple, fixed glass face. The needle is magnetized and points towards a small, stylized icon of a heart or anvil, symbolizing renewed vitality.

name: Gilded Dust Pouch Artifact
description: A small, worn leather pouch tied tightly with a simple leather thong. The edges and seams are subtly highlighted with faint gold flakes clinging to the material, symbolizing learned wealth.

name: Lantern-Light Opal Artifact
description: A small, oval brooch of polished silver. A centerpiece Opal gemstone displays a milky, translucent interior with a centralized light, inspiring strength and defense.

name: Iron-Bound Key Artifact
description: A large, antique key made of heavy, solid, unyielding iron. The key head is a simple square, and the thick teeth are slightly worn, suggesting it has opened many common caches.

name: Topaz Septstone Ring Artifact
description: A radiant ring focused purely on the acquisition and maximization of raw subterranean wealth, worn by merchant-thanes.

name: Amethyst of the Deep Mind Artifact
description: A thin circlet that aids mental clarity and the retention of beneficial enchantments during long, taxing delves.

name: Ruby of the First Fire Artifact
description: Worn by mid-level guards, channeling the primal heat of the earth to increase striking power.

name: Stamina of the Root-Bound Artifact
description: A robust buckle that links the wearers renewed vigor directly to their mechanical digging efficiency, maximizing sustained output.

name: The Geologist's Scope Artifact
description: A finely crafted lens used by surveyors to identify high-value pockets and maximize the recoverable yield from the ore found.

name: Hammerfall Sigil Artifact
description: A heavy medallion forged to resemble the mighty blow of a hammer, ensuring striking impacts are both powerful and brutally destructive.

name: Emerald Septstone Braid Artifact
description: Interwoven with glittering emeralds, this braid significantly enhances the chance to spot both gold and rare items.

name: Rune-Etched Timepiece Artifact
description: A complex, runic device that measures geological ages, making both mental and physical recovery faster.

name: Shaper's Thumb Ring Artifact
description: A tool-user's ring, enhancing the likelihood that helpful magic manifests and ensuring that its effect lasts for an extended period.

name: Dark Iron Chain Artifact
description: A heavy chain that encourages powerful, precise impacts, translating critical force directly into faster mining progression.

name: Khazad-dm Delving Charm Artifact
description: A weighted charm granting the deep, relentless speed necessary to match the tunneling pace of Morias early years.

name: Anvil of Songs Circlet Artifact
description: Forged in homage to one of the Great Tools, granting tireless endurance and making all blessings last longer in the dark.

name: Diamond Septstone of Kings Artifact
description: A potent ring symbolizing the highest wealth and the wisdom of the ruling Thanes, enhancing both resource quality and learned progression.

name: Brutal Picks Edge Artifact
description: A stylized brooch representing the power of the Brutal Pick, specializing in devastating, overwhelming critical strikes.

name: The Mithril Seeker's Compass Artifact
description: A rare instrument forged to detect the subtle magnetic signature of Mithril and other exotic ores, increasing discovery odds significantly.

name: Balin's Guard Chain Artifact
description: A heavy defense chain named after a respected leader, ensuring high combat readiness and powerful protective magic against deep threats.

name: Obsidian Scrutiny Band Artifact
description: A ring of deep obsidian, coupling the speed of deep drilling with the quick knowledge necessary to manage complex excavations safely.

name: The Shaping Hammer's Echo Artifact
description: Reflecting the persistence of the hammer blow, enhancing recovery and the chance of beneficial enchantments.

name: Deep Hearth Ember Artifact
description: Containing a piece of coal from an eternal hearth fire, this locket ensures massive gold yields are secured for the duration of supportive magic.

name: Durins Watch Earring Artifact
description: An heirloom worn by the descendants of Durin's Folk, focusing on disciplined, deadly combat effectiveness.

name: The Oath-Ring of the Undying Deep Artifact
description: Said to be the band worn by the very first dwarves, providing limitless endurance and rapidly learned ancestral knowledge, symbolizing the unextinguished ancestral hearth.

name: The Golden Coil of Ghamedu Artifact
description: A vast, heavy necklace representing the accumulated wealth of the first coastal settlements, guaranteeing maximum resource extraction quality and quantity.

name: Balrog's Toll Amulet Artifact
description: An item granting terrifying speed and destructive force, symbolizing the relentless deep tunneling that disturbed the demon of Moria. Maximum risk demands maximum velocity and combat readiness.

name: The Earthheart Forge Artifact
description: One of the Great Tools, this bracer channels immense geothermal heat for devastating combat power while simultaneously reinforcing the wearer's vitality, ensuring sustained conflict capability.

name: Nauglamrs Shadow Artifact
description: A piece crafted in homage to the lost Great Necklace, granting unparalleled ability to discover and claim the rarest and most valuable hidden materials, and sustaining all beneficial protective magic.
